==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Calycozoa
<hw>Cal`y*co*zo"a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <?/, <?/, cup or calyx a flower + <?/ animal.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A group of acalephs of which
<xex>Lucernaria</xex> is the type. The body is cup-shaped with eight
marginal lobes bearing clavate tentacles. An aboral sucker serves for
attachment. The interior is divided into four large compartments. See
<er>Lucernarida</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Calycular</ent>⟦br⟧
